Roles & Responsibilities
Job Description
Perform daily accounting & finance duties including receivables and payables processes, general ledger, tax and bank reconciliation, etc.;
Prepare monthly financial and management reports;
Consolidate accounts and ensure compliance with accounting standards;
Support audit and tax queries;
Liaise with banks on banking transactions;
Manage timely closing process and reconciliations;
Support the operational teams in maintaining strong vendor relationships.
Requirements
Diploma in Accounting & Finance or equivalent;
At least 3 years of experience in accounting & finance;
Strong understanding of accounting principles;
Ability to work in a dynamic environment;
Ability to work independently with a high degree of accuracy and efficiency;
Hands-on experience in cloud accounting systems such as AutoCount would be an advantage.

Roles & Responsibilities
Responsibilities:
Onboarding and setting up of new engagement.
Handle full set of accounts of a portfolio of clients individually or supported by assistants;
Handle month end closing for a portfolio of companies;
Preparation of monthly management accounts and reporting packages;
Handle/supervise a team of junior executives to handle day to day outsourced finance function, including AP processing, payroll, bookkeeping & accounting;
Consolidation of simple to complex group accounts;
Compilation of financial statements in accordance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards;
Assist in providing financial management services;
Advising clients on matters relating to finance operation, accounting system, accounting treatment and reporting when necessary;
Assist in consultancy and business advisory projects; and
Undertaking ad-hoc assignment assigned from time to time.
Requirement:
At least 4 years working experience in accountancy sector such as external audit, accounting outsourcing, fund accounting and administration etc within corporate service providers. Those with a mixture of experience as accountant in practice and accountant in business as well as in fund accounting are welcome to apply.
Degree in Accountancy, Singapore CA, ACCA, CPA Australia or their equivalent.
Well-versed with SFRS, IFRS and generally acceptable accounting practices.
Good knowledge of internal control within accounting system;
Sincere and committed, good time management and problem-solving skill, resourceful, proactive, able to work independently within fast-paced environment, effective verbal, and written communication skill.
Proficient in Microsoft Office applications and accounting and reporting software.
IT skillset, knowledge of accounting software, RPA and other modern automation tools are highly desired.
You may apply by sending your resume to siewinn@pkf.com

