Roles & Responsibilities
Manages dsm-firmenich long term business development with a major key global account in AMEA. Leads and manages the account on a regional level to grow sales and profitability according to the set global and regional objectives. Ensures that dsm-firmenich is recognized as the clients’ indispensable partner, identifies and delivers big bets while ensuring most efficient resource management. Contributes to the global strategy and supports agreed ways of working and governance.
At dsm-firmenich people are at the heart of the company. We are committed to equal employment opportunities and value diversity in the workplace.
Key Responsibilities:
· Leads the business strategy and growth for AMEA and coordinates the local country account manager activities with the NEA, SEA and IMA regions and develops & executes strategy with clear milestones where to play and how to win;
· Be the customers’ ‘voice’ within dsm-firmenich, issuing comprehensive action reports and effectively communicating with all internal partners: Technical, Creation, Marketing, Innovation, Pricing, Operations;
· Best-in-class project management in close collaboration with the BU teams and support functions to deliver big bets;
· Develops strong network within customer to result into successful long term business relationship and client retention;
· Continuously identifies and unlocks new business opportunities along the entire value chain, including disruptive innovation ideas to generate productivity savings & margin improvement;
· Positions dsm-firmenich Innovation Programs underpinned by sensory, consumer and category insights to drive vitality & regional pipeline growth;
· Develops sales forecast, builds annual budget and closely monitors & actions on margin targets;
· Maintains and develops strong network within customer network which continues to result in a successful long term business relationship;
· Constantly seeks new business opportunities along the entire value chain, including disruptive innovation ideas;
· Contributes to validate the requirements for the identification and selection of new technologies/solutions;
· Drives Taste, Texture and Health development projects together with all internal partners proactively.
· Continuously improve & re-invent “best in class” collaboration model.
We bring:
· A rich history and a promising future of bold scientific innovation and passionate creation with our customers;
· A space to grow by encouraging and supporting curiosity and an open mindset;
· The opportunity to work for a company where sustainability is much more than a claim and is core to our strategy and purpose;
· Barrier-free communities within our organization where every employee is equally valued and respected – regardless of their background, beliefs, or identity;
· A firm belief that working together with our customers is the key to achieving great things;
· An eagerness to be one team and learn from each other to bring progress to life and create a better future.
You bring:
· Over 10 years of successful experience in the international Food industry
· Bachelor’s degree in Business or equivalent
· Strong drive for results and client focus
· Strategic and disruptive thinking
· Strong interpersonal and relationship skills
· Ability to develop successful and sustainable client relationship with large accounts
· Strong business acumen and entrepreneurial mindset
· Advanced Sales and Negotiation skills
· Technical background preferred

Roles & Responsibilities
Who we are:

ACT is the world’s leading provider of market-based sustainability solutions. As enablers of the global energy transition, we help organizations hit their climate targets and maximize their profits while reducing risk. Since 2009, we have become a trusted brand in climate projects, green electricity markets, renewable energies and energy efficiency, renewable fuels, emission allowances, and carbon credits.

From our offices in Amsterdam, New York, Singapore, Shanghai, and Paris, we draw on over a decade of market knowledge to deliver tailor-made solutions and sterling service. Business Development Associates work in region-specific teams to create product portfolios for clients that meet their specific needs and help them drive climate action their way.

What you’ll do:

As a Corporate Account Manager you will create, manage and grow your own portfolio of clients. Creating this portfolio will come with a lot of business development and relationship management, which means that every day brings its own dynamics. You will work with both new and existing clients in the market on the broad range of solutions for their various sustainability challenges.
Act as the key contact point for clients to consult and educate clients on different sustainability solutions such as carbon credits and renewable energy certificates.
Develop sales strategies by conducting market profiling to identify potential market for various environmental products.
Explore and identify new business opportunities through various channels/methods
Enhance existing customers portfolio by understanding customers business cycle, perform frequent follow ups and maintaining good rapport with customers.
Facilitate negotiation of sale agreements within limits and present proposal to prospective clients.
Monitor competition landscape, build relationships with industry players and expand business network to support partnership strategies.
Keep updated with market changes and industry updates.
What we’re looking for:
A Bachelor’s / Master's graduate, preferably in Business, Economics, or Finance;
3 years’ experience in Corporate Sales / Business Development / Soft Commodities;
Consulting experience in ESG and ability to speak multiple languages would be an added advantage;
Entrepreneurial mindset and thrives in high pressured environment;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Affinity in sales, business development and commodities;
Enthusiastic in generating leads and cold calling;
Accountability, responsibility, and openness to learning fast.
